From {{inh|en|enm|Èellen}}, {{m|enm|yellen}}, from {{inh|en|ang|Ä¡iellan}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*gellanÄ…}}. Cognate with {{cog|stq|gÃ¤lje|t=to yell}}, {{cog|nl|gillen|t=to yell}}, {{cog|nds-de|gellen|t=to yell}}, {{cog|de|gellen|t=to yell}}.
====Verb====
{{en-verb}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} shout; holler; make a loud sound with the voice.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} to convey by shouting
#:{{ux|en|He '''yelled''' directions to the party from the car.}}
# {{lb|en|slang}} to [[tell someone off]] (in a loud and angry manner)
#:{{ux|en|If I come home late again, my dad is gonna '''yell''' at me.}}
=====Usage notes=====
To yell '''at''' someone is as in a hostile manner, while to yell '''to''' someone means to speak loudly so as to be heard.
